.TH CODEX_CLOUD 1 "July 2026" "codex-cli 0.142.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codex\-cloud \- [EXPERIMENTAL] Browse tasks from Codex Cloud and apply changes locally
.SH SYNOPSIS
.EX
Usage: codex cloud [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
[EXPERIMENTAL] Browse tasks from Codex Cloud and apply changes locally
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B exec
Submit a new Codex Cloud task without launching the TUI
.TP
.B status
Show the status of a Codex Cloud task
.TP
.B list
List Codex Cloud tasks
.TP
.B apply
Apply the diff for a Codex Cloud task locally
.TP
.B diff
Show the unified diff for a Codex Cloud task
.TP
.B help
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config <key=value>
Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`. Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.
.PP
Examples: \- `\-c model="o3"` \- `\-c 'sandbox_permissions=["disk\-full\-read\-access"]'` \- `\-c shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`
.TP
.B \-\-enable <FEATURE>
Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=true`
.TP
.B \-\-disable <FEATURE>
Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=false`
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help (see a summary with '\-h')
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1),
.BR codex\-cloud\-exec (1),
.BR codex\-cloud\-status (1),
.BR codex\-cloud\-list (1),
.BR codex\-cloud\-apply (1),
.BR codex\-cloud\-diff (1)
